explain the error handling flow in the project
1. Client sends request
        ↓
2. Request hits Express Route
        ↓
3. Route handler is wrapped with asyncWrapper
        ↓
4. asyncWrapper executes the async function
        ↓
5. Async operation runs (DB call / logic)
        ↓
6. ❌ If NO error → response sent normally
        ↓
   ✅ If ERROR occurs:
        ↓
7. Promise catches error inside asyncWrapper
        ↓
8. next(error) is called
        ↓
9. Express skips all normal middleware/routes
        ↓
10. Control goes to Error Handling Middleware
        ↓
11. Error middleware processes error
        ↓
12. Sends response (status + message)
        ↓
13. Client receives error response


Async Function throws error
        ↓
Converted to Promise.reject(error)
        ↓
.catch(next)
        ↓
next(error)
